# Data, Migrations, and Performance

## Database Safety
- Parameterize all queries; never concatenate untrusted input into SQL/NoSQL statements.
- Use transactions for multi-step writes that must remain consistent.
- Require explicit approval and a documented rollback plan before executing
 destructive schema changes or high-risk data operations.
- Avoid unbounded bulk `UPDATE`/`DELETE`; always include safeguarding conditions.

## Performance
- Consider algorithmic complexity (time and space) for data-intensive operations.
- Prevent N+1 query patterns and over-fetching; paginate or stream large datasets.
- Use async/non-blocking I/O patterns in latency-sensitive or high-throughput paths.
- Avoid loading large datasets entirely into memory when streaming is viable.
- Reduce unnecessary re-computation; cache deterministic results where appropriate.
